records.addlTxt:
Defendant Cameron Dejhoure Bateman in court with attorney Christian Thomas Eichenlaub.  Megan Patricia Carmody appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Negotiations placed on the record.  Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Sentencing proceeded. Statements made by State, defense and defendant. 
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  6 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE with any other time being served with credit for 29 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 3 YEARS and 6 MONTHS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 YEARS and 6 MONTHS.

The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but is not eligible the Substance Abuse Program, only after serving the first 2 years of this sentence.

Court stayed the sentence and placed the defendant on 4 YEARS probation. Defendant is eligible for dosage probation.


CONDITIONS OF PROBATION or EXTENDED SUPERVISION IF REVOKED:
* 1 YEAR in the House of Corrections condition time. No electronic monitoring. No goodtime. The first 6 MONTHS are STRAIGHT TIME, the last 6 MONTHS the Court will allow for release to the Day Reporting Center for programming.  
* No contact with victims or Subway as specified in the criminal complaint;
*Provide DNA sample;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Random urine screens;
*No drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Participate in a cognitive thinking program;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs. However, Court waived the DNA surcharge because the defendant provided a sample voluntarily prior to being ordered by the Court; 
  - Cash bail on deposit to be applied, any extra to be returned to the remitter;  
  - If revoked, the Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision. DOC shall collect those sums.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.


Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he/she may never possess a firearm. 
Court advised defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.
Court advised defendant that he/she may not vote until his/her civil rights have been restored.  

Filed;
-Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
-Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
-Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
-Letter in support of the defendant

Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.
